aten Army at Thermpylae  United Service Magazine n s  15  121  April 1987  pp  576 ff  Prentice  W K   Thermopylae  Classical Review 57 2  Sept  1943  63 66  Pritchett  W  Kendrick   New Light on Thermypylae  AJA 62 2  April  1958  203 213  Rosser  J   The role of the Great Isthmus corridor in the Slavonic invasions of Greece  ByzF 9  1985  245 253  Sacks  Kenneth K   Herodotus and the Dating of the Battle of Thermopylae  Classical Quarterly n s  26 2  1976  pp  232ff  Stanford  W B   Epitaph on the Slain at Thermopylae  Hermathena 55  1940  pp  90ff  Szemler  G J  Cherf  W J  and Kraft  J C  Thermopylai  Myth and Reality in 480 B C  Chicago  Ares  1996  Wallace  Paul W   The Anopaia Path and Thermopylae  AJA 84 1  January 1980  pp  15 23  Artemesium Wallace  P W   Aphetai and the Battle of Artemesion  Stud pres  to S  Dow 305 310 Rigsby  K J  GRBS Suppl 1984  Salamis cf  Markov  Battles of World History  New York  1979  Green  Peter The Year of Salamis  London  1970                          Xerxes at Salamis Plataea Grundy  G  B  The Topography of the Battle of Plataea  London  1894  Hunt  P   Helots at the Battle of Plataea  Historia 46  1997  pp  129 144  J F  Lazenby  The Spartan Army  Warminster  England  Aris   Phillips 1985  Chapter 5 H B  Wright  The Campaign of Plataea  New Haven  1904  Mycale MacDougall  I   The Persian Ships at Mycale  in Essays Presented to K J Dover  pp  143 149  Peloponnesian Wars Kagan  Donald  The Archidamian War  Ithaca  1974  Kagan  Donald  The Peace of Nicias and the Sicilian Expedition Kagan  Donald  The Fall of the Athenian Empire Kagan  Donald  The Outbreak of the Peloponnesian War Panagopoulos   Fugutives and Refugees in the PeloponnesianWar  EEAth xxvii 1979  1980  247 296  Strauss  B S  Athens After the Peloponnesian War  reviewed by A M  Devine in CP 83 1988  Sphacteria Sicilian Expedition Green  Peter The Armada from Athens London  1971  Kagan  Donald  The Peace of Nicias and the Sicilian Expedition Ithaca  1981  Arginuae 